   <LINES>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>This class is intended to be used my multiple applications to cater for</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>some of the most basic functions in regard to outputting data to the</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>user. This way we do not have to code the same things repeatedly in each</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>program.</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>There are three main functions of this class at the moment:-</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>(1) To output either a standard SAP error message, or free text of an</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>error where there is no standard SAP message, and decide whether to show</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>this to the user or write it to the log if a job is running in the</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>background.</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>(2) To show a user a progress indicator whilst processing large internal</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>tables.</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>(3) To output an error log in a variety of situations.</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
   </LINES>
